test_setup_details.test_setup_details_caption: <big>MANAGING TIME - </big>Rate management of time, self -direction.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Follows regular schedule for bedtime, wake-up, meal times. Rarely tardy or absent for work, day programs, appointments, scheduled activities.

<big>HOUSING STABILITY/MAINTENANCE - </big>Rate self-sufficiency for maintaining independent and adequate housing, management of household.   Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Maintains stable housing.  Organizes possessions. Cleans. Abides by rules and contributes to maintenance if living with others.

<big>COMMUNICATION - </big>Rate ongoing and effective verbal and nonverbal communication Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Listens to people.  Expresses opinions/feelings. Makes wishes known effectively.

<big>ALCOHOL/DRUG USE - </big>Rate self-control in maintenance of alcohol/drug abstinence or safe use.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Avoids abuse or abstains from alcohol/drugs, cigarettes. Understands signs and symptoms of abuse or dependency. Avoids misuse or combining alcohol, drugs, medication.

<big>PRODUCTIVITY - </big>Rate functioning primarily in most appropriate expected role (i.e. wage earner, homemaker, student).  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Independently working, volunteering, homemaking, or learning skills for financial self support.

• Using the scale below, rate how often or how well the consumer independently performed or managed each of the 20 Activities of Daily Living (ADL's) in the community during the last 30 days. If the consumer's level of functioning is varied, rate the lower score. Consider impairments in functioning due to physical limitations as well as those due to mental impairments. Do not consider environmental limitations (eg, "no jobs available").
  • Strengths are scored as 5 or greater in an activity and indicates functioning "within normal limits" (WNL) for that activity.
  • All DLA's are applicable. Enter NA only if the activity was not assessed. Do not score more than 5 DLA's as NA.

<big>COMMUNITY RESOURCES - </big>Rate independent use of community resources (e.g. health & social services, shopping, transportation).  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Uses other community services. Self help groups. Telephone, public transportation, religious organizations, shopping.

<big>DRESS - </big>Rate independent maintenance of appropriate dress.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Dresses self. Wears clean clothes that are appropriate for weather, job, and other activities. Clothing is generally neat and intact.
<big>NUTRITION - </big>Rate independent management of nutritional needs.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Eats at least 2 basically nutritious meals daily.

<big>SOCIAL NETWORK - </big>Rate quality of interactions with immediate social network (e.g. close friends).  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Gets along with friends, neighbors, co-workers, other peers.

<big>COPING SKILLS - </big>Rate effective use of coping mechanisms.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Knows about nature of disability/illness, probable limitations, symptoms of relapse. Behaviors that cause relapse or make things worse. Options for coping, improving, preventing relapse, restoring feelings of self-worth, competence, being in control.

<big>GROOMING - </big>Rate independent care and grooming of hair, hands, general appearance.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Care for hair, hands, general appearance. Shaves.

<big>HEALTH PRACTICES - </big>Rate independent   self-care for physical and mental health, including treatment plan compliance, medication compliance.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Takes care of health issues.  Manages moods, infections. Takes medication as prescribed. Follows up on medical appointments.

<big>SEXUALITY - </big>Rate sexual health, sexually appropriate, safe interactions.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Appropriate behavior towards others. Comfortable with gender. Respects privacy and rights of others. Practices safe sex or abstains.

<big>LEISURE - </big>Rate independent participation in leisure activities.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Relaxes with a variety of activities. Attends/participates in sports or performing arts events. Reads newspapers, magazines, books. Recreational games with others. Involved with arts/crafts. Goes to movies.

<big>SAFETY - </big>Rate maintenance of personal safety.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Safely moves about community-adequate vision, hearing, makes safe decisions. Safely uses small appliances, ovens/burners, matches, knives, razors, other tools.

<big>MANAGING MONEY - </big>Rate independent management of personal finances
Rate management of time, self -direction.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Manages money wisely.  Has an independent source of funds. Controls spending habits.

<big>FAMILY RELATIONSHIPS - </big>Rate family interactions, quality of family relationship.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Gets along with family.  Positive relationships as parent, sibling, child, significant other, family member.

• None of the time. Extremely severe impairment or problems in functioning. Pervasive level of continuous paid supports needed.
  • A little of the time. Severe impairment or problems in functioning. Extensive level of continuous paid supports needed.
  • Occasionally. Moderately severe impairment or problems in functioning. Moderate level of continuous paid supports needed.
  • Some of the time. Moderate impairment or problems in functioning. Low level of continuous paid supports needed.
  • (WNL) - A good bit of the time. Mild impairment or problems in functioning. Moderate level of intermittent paid supports needed.
  • (WNL) - Most of the time. Very mild impairments or problems in functioning. Low level of intermittent paid supports needed.
  • (WNL) - All of the time. Independently managed DLA in community. No impairment or problem in functioning requiring paid supports.

<big>PROBLEM SOLVING - </big>Rate independent management of problems of daily living.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Resolves basic problems of daily living. Asks questions for clarity and setting expectations.

<big>BEHAVIORAL NORMS - </big>Rate extended social network relationships, interaction with community.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Complies with community norms, probation/parole, court requirements, if applicable. Controls dangerous, violent, aggressive, bizarre or nuisance behaviors. Respects rights of others.

<big>PERSONAL HYGIENE - </big>Rate independent healthcare of personal hygiene, dental and oral care.  Examples of Scoring Strengths as WNL behaviors (Scores of 5, 6, 7) - Care for personal cleanliness, such as bathing, brushing teeth.
